      "writtenOn": "2015-02-27T13:43:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not sure that name should be a query parameter or part of the resource, as in \n\nGET /v2.0/metrics/names/{name}?dimensions\n\nI think it should be the latter though.\n\nIf you supply a nem dont\u0027 you just get one metric back though. Isn\u0027t \"name\" as a query parameter pretty useless?\n\nHowever, I didn\u0027t think we were going to add query parameters to this right now as in just give me all the names.",
      "revId": "7fe5df2e1b6aeeee05381d55ebcc0580e3dcb2f3",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ba7be1f8_f5ce9bb3",
        "filename": "docs/monasca-api-spec.md",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 941,
      "author": {
        "id": 14517
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-02-27T16:30:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The thought was to allow filtering by dimensions, but the system currently requires a name if dimensions are present. Additionally, influx would support regular expressions for the name parameter, if our api allowed it, which could be very useful. I\u0027m planning on looking into both of these afterwards.",
      "parentUuid": "ba7be1f8_7e57f526",
      "revId": "7fe5df2e1b6aeeee05381d55ebcc0580e3dcb2f3",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ba7be1f8_0ba3f69e",
        "filename": "docs/monasca-api-spec.md",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 941,
      "author": {
        "id": 2419
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-02-28T14:37:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think filtering by dimensions is useful.\n\nI\u0027m not sure the query \n\nGET /v2.0/metrics/names/{name} is useful\n\nAll we are doing is returning an array of names in the JSON response, so if the name exists in thiscase, you would get an array back with one element in it. \n\nI could see how regex on names is useful, as in give me all the metric names that match \"cpu.*\". That would be modeled as a query filter parameter.",
      "parentUuid": "ba7be1f8_f5ce9bb3",
      "revId": "7fe5df2e1b6aeeee05381d55ebcc0580e3dcb2f3",
      "serverId": "4a232e18-c5a9-48ee-94c0-e04e7cca6543",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ba7be1f8_393917d9",
        "filename": "docs/monasca-api-spec.md",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 942,
